label: YRD220
info_overview: The Yale Real Living Stand-alone Touchscreen Deadbolt Lock combines a robust lockset with a contemporary aesthetic.
info_inclusion:
To include the lock in a Z-Wave Network (taken from the installation manual:

  1. Touch the lock screen to activate
  2. Enter the master pin and press #
  3. Press 7, then #
  4. Press 1, then #

The lock will now be in inclusion mode.
info_exclusion:
To exclude the lock from a Z-Wave Network (taken from the installation manual:

  1. Touch the lock screen to activate
  2. Enter the master pin and press #
  3. Press 7, then #
  4. Press 3, then #

The lock will now be in exclusion mode.
category_description: Devices whose primary pupose is locking something

parameters.label: Audio Volume
parameters.description: Sets the volume level of the beeps and voice prompts

parameters.label: Auto Re-lock
parameters.description: When enabled, the unit will automatically re-lock

parameters.label: Re-lock Time
parameters.description: Time after unlocking that the device will lock

parameters.label: Wrong Code Entry Limit
parameters.description: The number of invalid tries before the lock shutdowns and sends an alarm

parameters.label: Language
parameters.description: Language used by the voice prompts

parameters.label: Shutdown Time
parameters.description: Number of times the device is locked out after the invalid retries are exceeded

parameters.label: Operating Mode
parameters.description: Sets if the unit operates normal, or disables keypad and Z-Wave lock/unlock
parameters.overview:
0 = Normal

1 = Vacation Mode (User Codes Disabled)

2 = Privacy Mode (User Codes and ZWave Codes Disabled

associations.label: Alarm Reports
associations.description: Alarm reports are sent out to all devices in the association group

documents.label: Yale Real Living Touchscreen Deadbolt Installation Manual
